# 📊 Dashboard Visualizations

## 👨‍💼 Gender-wise Distribution
🥧 Pie Chart

Shows the percentage of Male and Female respondents.

### 🔍 Insight
- Female respondents represent around **63%**
- Male respondents represent around **37%**

---

## 💰 Investment Avenue

📊 Column Chart

Shows whether respondents prefer investing or not.

### 🔍 Insight
- Majority of respondents prefer investing.
- Very few respondents do not invest.

---

## ⏳ Investment Duration

📉 Bar Chart

Analyzes preferred investment duration.

### 🔍 Insight
- Most investors prefer **3–5 years**.
- The second preferred duration is **1–3 years**.
- Very few invest for less than one year or more than five years.

---

## 🎯 Investment Objective

🍩 Doughnut Chart

Displays the primary investment objectives.

### 🔍 Insight
- 💰 Capital Appreciation is the most preferred objective.
- 📈 Income Generation is the second preference.
- 🌱 Growth receives comparatively fewer responses.

---

## 💼 Investment Purpose

📊 Column Chart

Shows why people invest.

### 🔍 Insight
- 🏆 Wealth Creation is the top investment purpose.
- 💼 Saving for the Future ranks second.
- 💵 Regular Returns are the least selected.

---

## 🏦 Savings Objective

📈 Area Chart

Displays the financial goals of respondents.

### 🔍 Insight
- 🏖️ Retirement Planning is the most common saving objective.
- 🏥 Health Care ranks second.
- 🎓 Education receives the fewest responses.

---

## 📈 Expected Returns

🥧 Pie Chart

Shows respondents' expected return percentages.

### 🔍 Insight
- ⭐ 20%–30% expected return is the most popular.
- 📈 30%–40% is the second preference.
- 📉 10%–20% is selected by the fewest respondents.

---

# 📌 Key Insights

✅ Majority of respondents are Female.

✅ Most people actively invest their money.

✅ Capital Appreciation is the biggest investment objective.

✅ Wealth Creation is the primary reason for investing.

✅ Retirement Planning is the leading savings goal.

✅ Most investors prefer a **3–5 year** investment period.

✅ Expected annual returns of **20%–30%** are the most common preference.

